gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 79, Knicks 73
gameRecap.excerpt: The 76ers defeated the Knicks, 79-73. Kelly Oubre Jr. notched 18 points, 10 rebounds, three assists and three steals for the 76ers, while Buddy Hield added 16 points (4-6 3PT FG) and seven rebounds in the victory. Jalen Brunson tallied 19 points and eight assists for the Knicks in the losing effort. The 76ers snap a three-game losing streak as they improve to 36-28 on the season, while the Knicks fall to 37-27.
